B.chapter(3,"The Black Problem: The Najdorf","Your largest leak, treated first.")
B.para("We start here because this is where your rating is bleeding. The Najdorf Sicilian is the most respected "
    "defence to 1.e4 in chess history, played by Fischer and Kasparov, and the reason is simple: it fights for the "
    "initiative from move one while keeping a sound, flexible structure. It suits you - it is sharp, it is "
    "principled, and it rewards exactly the tactical alertness you already have. But it must be understood, not "
    "memorised. Here is the understanding.")
B.sec("The moves, and the idea behind each")
B.para("1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6. Take the moves one idea at a time. With 1...c5 you refuse "
